Effect of single-dose methotrexate on ovarian reserve in women with ectopic pregnancy. To evaluate ovarian reserve in women with ectopic pregnancy treated with single-dose systemic methotrexate in the early post-treatment period.Prospective study.Women's health education and research hospital.Eighty-two patients with ectopic pregnancy and 80 healthy women in the same age group were included in the study. Of the 82 patients, 49 with ectopic pregnancy were treated with single-dose systemic methotrexate (MTX) and 33 were treated surgically with laparoscopy or laparotomy (salpingectomy or salpingostomy).Ovarian reserve testing.Basal FSH on the 3rd day of the menstrual cycle, E₂, basal antral follicle count (AFC), and ovarian volume.There were no differences among the groups in terms of basal FSH, E₂, AFC, and ovarian volume.The single-dose MTX treatment had no effect on ovarian reserve in women with ectopic pregnancy as measured by the above-mentioned parameters.